summary: An ordinance accepting a deed to the City of Seattle executed on William Clausen and Josephine Clausen, his wife, and Herman Horn and Dorotha Horn, his wife, to the City of Georgetown (now the City of Seattle) dated April 11, 1910, to the east 5 feet of tract 4, of Wilson and Bryan's Tracts, all in the City of Georgetown (now the City of Seattle), King County, Washington, for street purposes only.
